26/10/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- Prime Minister Fatos Nano said Monday (25 October) Euro-Atlantic integration remains the government's main priority and strategic target. 
Nano met with visiting Croatian Defence Minister Berislav Roncevic and said NATO enlargement provides the region with the opportunity to leave behind historical conflicts and take the road of progress and prosperity.
In other news, Montenegrin President Filip Vujanovic started a two-day visit to Tirana on Monday. 
He met with his Albanian counterpart, Alfred Moisiu, to discuss strengthening bilateral ties in the fields of economics, politics and culture. 
(ATA, HINA, MINA - 25/10/04)
